 as they carry beyond music by working through music to wider philosophical and cultural questions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aMusicxPhilosophy and aesthetics. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  aaesthetics.  abeauty.  acase studies.  aclassical music.  aclassical repertoire.  aconcept of music.  aentertainment industry.  aessay.  aformalist approaches.  ahermeneutic approaches.  amodern culture.  amusic culture.  amusic historians.  amusic interpretation.  amusic philosophy.  amusic scholars.  amusic.  amusical meaning.  amusical performance.  amusical scores.  amusical work.  amusicians.  anonfiction.  aopera.  aperformativity.  aperforming arts.  aperforming music.  athought provoking.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026706040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094736840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947368423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947368/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY